Loops 
- Loops are used to repeat a block of code multiple times

1. While Loop / unknown amount of rept.
    - Checks the condition first
    - If the condition is true, it will run the code block
    - Repeats until the condition becomes false

    Syntax: 
    while (condition) 
        { // code to repeat }

 2. Do-While Loop / must happen once
    - Runs the code at least once
    - Then checks the condition

    Syntax:
        do {
            //code 
        } while (condition)
***Even if the condition is false, it runs once***

3. for Loop / fixed number of rept. 
    - Defined number of times loop 
    - Start value, Check condition, Run code, Update value

    Syntax:
        for (initialization; condition; update)
        {
            code to repeat 
        }

4. For Each Loop (Array)
Syntax: for (dataType variableName : arrayName)
{
    code to be repeated
}
